design:
**Current Implementation (ListScreen.tsx:139-245):**
- Single `useInput` handler processes all keystrokes
- `showTagFilter` is just a visibility toggle
- No concept of "input mode" that captures keyboard focus

**Solution - Implement Input Mode State:**

1. Add `inputMode` state similar to SearchScreen.tsx pattern:
```tsx
type InputMode = "list" | "tagFilter" | "search";
const [inputMode, setInputMode] = useState<InputMode>("list");
```

2. Modify `useInput` handler to check mode first:
```tsx
useInput((input, key) => {
  if (key.escape) {
    if (inputMode !== "list") {
      setInputMode("list");
      setShowTagFilter(false);
      return;
    }
  }

  // Only process list navigation when in list mode
  if (inputMode === "tagFilter") {
    // Handle tag filter specific input
    return;
  }

  // Normal list keybinds
  if (input === "t") {
    setInputMode("tagFilter");
    setShowTagFilter(true);
    return;
  }
  // ... other keybinds
});
```

3. Add TextInput component for tag filter when in tagFilter mode:
```tsx
{showTagFilter && inputMode === "tagFilter" && (
  <Box>
    <TextInput 
      value={tagFilterQuery} 
      onChange={setTagFilterQuery}
      focused={true}
    />
  </Box>
)}
```

