## Problem
Claude Code allows skills with just SKILL.md (frontmatter provides metadata).
Grimoire requires skill.yaml, breaking compatibility with many skills.

## Claude Code Valid Skill
```
my-skill/
└── SKILL.md   # Has frontmatter with name, description
```

## Current Grimoire Behavior
```typescript
// skill-cache-service.ts - FAILS without skill.yaml
const manifestPath = join(path, "skill.yaml");
```

## Implementation
1. Try skill.yaml first
2. If not found, try SKILL.md
3. Parse YAML frontmatter from SKILL.md
4. Create synthetic manifest from frontmatter

```typescript
const getManifest = async (skillDir) => {
  const yamlPath = join(skillDir, "skill.yaml");
  if (await exists(yamlPath)) {
    return parseYaml(yamlPath);
  }

  const skillMdPath = join(skillDir, "SKILL.md");
  if (await exists(skillMdPath)) {
    const content = await readFile(skillMdPath);
    const frontmatter = parseFrontmatter(content);
    return {
      name: frontmatter.name,
      version: "1.0.0", // Default
      description: frontmatter.description,
      type: "prompt",
      allowed_tools: frontmatter["allowed-tools"]?.split(","),
    };
  }

  throw new Error("No skill.yaml or SKILL.md found");
};
```

